{"type": "article", "id": 29835, "title": "网球制成的音响", "description": "", "date": "2016-07-19T23:03:58Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [], "category": 25, "column": 28, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 0, "praise_count": 15, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160719222907nl50uXdRKgBoU4iq.jpg", "contents": "<p>          </p><p>我们上个月介绍过一款会让足球迷惊喜的<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/28095.html\">腕带</a>，来自伦敦的 Rogue Projects 工作室同样有一个变废为宝的点子，不过关注点却有所不同：根据调查，每年仅在温网赛场上废弃的网球就高达 55000 个，为了让这些“退休”的网球有更好的归处，他们曾设想过好几个创意，最终决定将球制作成便携式无线音响 <a href=\"http://www.hearospeaker.com/home/\" rel=\"nofollow\">hearO</a>。网球硬度和中空的设计让它们本身就成为了保护硬件的良好外壳，独特的材质也有助于音响在高频部分和声音形成共振。在法国工房 Innov8 的帮助下，设计师们对每个网球进行了改造，同时最大限度地保留原始的外观，斐波那契螺旋形的音响口与网球也契合得非常自然。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/rogueprojects/hearo-a-wireless-speaker-in-a-championship-tennis\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，最低价为 50 英镑。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160719222945gf1Tbw9Me04Blpx8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562130\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160719222945BcpsjlCf64q5XVTx.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563609\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160719222945PeTIvYFyUgdqSC3w.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665623\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160719222945IxzHDgP20hLwkJC9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667647\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}